<p><a name="Legend" id="Legend"></a></p>
<h3><span class="editsection">[<a href="/w/index.php?title=Acadians&amp;action=edit&amp;section=7" title="Edit section: Legend">edit</a>]</span> <span class="mw-headline">Legend</span></h3>
<p>The American <a href="/wiki/Folk_hero" title="Folk hero">folklore hero</a>, <a href="/wiki/Paul_Bunyan_(lumberjack)" title="Paul Bunyan (lumberjack)" class="mw-redirect">Paul Bunyan</a>, is believed by some to have been influenced if not inspired by Acadian stories about <a href="/wiki/Lumberjack" title="Lumberjack">lumberjacks</a> in the <a href="/wiki/Detroit" title="Detroit">Detroit</a> area, around the 1910s.<sup class="noprint Template-Fact"><span title="This claim needs references to reliable sources&#160;since July 2008" style="white-space: nowrap;">[<i><a href="/wiki/Wikipedia:Citation_needed" title="Wikipedia:Citation needed">citation needed</a></i>]</span></sup></p>
